external_knowledge:
- "Above-average wins" refers to the number of wins greater than the average number of wins across all teams;
- "Scheduled opponents" refers to teams that have an opponent listed in their schedule;
- "Recorded scores" refers to games where the score has been documented;
- "Athletic directors' contact information" includes the athletic directors' usernames and emails.

- 'Top-level' teams refer to Varsity teams;
- The ranking is based on the points earned by the teams;
- The query only considers the top three teams in each sport.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT wins
FROM standings
ORDER BY wins DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "top 3 teams" refers to the teams ranked highest based on points and goals scored;
- "faced their most recent opponent" refers to the latest schedule entry for each team;
- "titans of the game" is a metaphorical expression to highlight the top-performing teams.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS teams_with_more_wins_than_losses
FROM standings
WHERE wins > losses;

external_knowledge:
- "Cumulative points" refer to the total points earned by a team, calculated over the season or a specific period;
- "Rank within their schools" means the position of a team compared to other teams from the same school, based on points;
- "Played more than 5 games" indicates that the team has participated in at least 6 games.
